<HEADLINE>
FT  02 FEB 93 / The Lex Column: Unilever
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Much time and thought went into Unilever's head office review as the
Anglo-Dutch giant continued to wage war on bureaucracy. But it is perhaps
surprising that the outcome was not more radical.
Unilever has devolved greater management responsibility to the operating
level. But it has preserved the cumbersome division and duplication of
functions between London and Rotterdam. Reasons of tax and history make this
a particularly knotty problem. But the incoming co-chairman, Mr Michael
Perry, had a fine opportunity to remould Unilever in a far more inventive
spirit. It is a pity he did not take it.
