<HEADLINE>
FT  01 FEB 93 / International Company News: Greyfriars nav dips on repayment
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SHARES IN Greyfriars Investment dropped 2p to 15p on Friday after it
announced that an early repayment of a loan note had reduced the net asset
value by 5.4p.
Investment trusts borrow money - 'gear up' is the jargon - when they believe
that the return on equities will outweigh those on fixed interest. However,
the loan note was deep discounted and its repayment entitlement is growing
at 13 per cent a year.
The terms of the loan notes include a covenant; although that has not been
breached, the company repaid half the loan note in August last year, and has
decided it was prudent to pay off the other half now.
</TEXT>
