<HEADLINE>
FT  01 FEB 93 / Observer: Driving force
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Legend already has it that while Bill Clinton was out driving with his wife
before the inauguration, he pulled into a busy filling station for fuel.
Hillary, thinking herself less likely to draw unwelcome attention, got out
and filled up then went to one of the paybooths where, to her husband's
annoyance, she spent a long time chatting familiarly to the man at the till.
'What a coincidence,' she said on returning. 'We were at college together -
in fact, I dated him until I met you.'
'So if I hadn't come along, you'd now be married to a gas station
attendant,' said her husband. 'No,' she replied, 'I'd be married to the
president of the US.'
</TEXT>
