<HEADLINE>
FT  01 FEB 93 / Construction Contracts: Pounds 24.5m housing projects for
Lovell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The partnerships division of the LOVELL GROUP has won a series of contracts
across England and Wales in partnership with local authorities and housing
associations worth Pounds 24.5m.
The projects will provide 768 units of affordable social housing for rent,
shared ownership and sale to local authority and housing association tenants
and those on waiting lists.
The largest group of work for a single client is in south Wales for SHAW
Home Care Housing Association where the partnership in six schemes worth
Pounds 5.88m will produce a combination of 225 family houses, flats and
bedsitting rooms for elderly people at Caerphilly, Pontypool, Newport,
Brackla, Port Talbot and Bridgend.
In the west and south west 42 new and refurbished flats are being
constructed at Plymouth with Cornwall Housing Association at a cost of
Pounds 2.59m; in Wiltshire, 10 dwellings at Castle Coombe for English
Villages Housing Association (Pounds 396,000) and 25 homes at Amesbury for
Shaftesbury Society Housing Association (Pounds 941,000); and at Kemble 18
units valued at Pounds 700,000 will be built in collaboration with
Gloucestershire Housing Association.
In the Midlands, Lovell Partnerships is also working on a Pounds 1.12m
project with the Gloucestershire Housing Association at Cheltenham to
provide 39 units; at Uttoxeter 51 units will be built in a four-way
partnership and 16 bungalows will be constructed at Burton-upon-Trent.
