<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JAN 93 / Chinese invited to Taiwan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Taiwan will invite mainland Chinese trade officials to a meeting next month
under the auspices of the Asia Pacific Economic Co-operation (APEC) forum,
the Board of Foreign Trade said yesterday, reports Reuter from Taipei.
They would be the first Chinese officials to make a formal visit to Taiwan
since the end of the Chinese civil war in 1949, said Mr Peter Ho, a section
chief at the board. However, he said the three Chinese participants would
not hold bilateral talks with Taiwanese officials.
They would be invited to attend a training course on the development of
small and medium-sized enterprises in Taipei from February 27 to March 2.
