<HEADLINE>
FT  30 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Raglan Property
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Raglan Property Trust cut its pre-tax loss from Pounds 685,000 to Pounds
564,000 in the six months ended September 30 1992. Losses per share were
clipped from 0.4p to 0.3p.
The company continued to unwind outstanding liabilities initiated in the
late 1980s, and recently exchanged an agreement with Tesco whereby Raglan
was released from its obligation to purchase properties for Pounds 4.5m in
the centre of Cirencester.
Discussions with lending banks and Tameside continue. If successful, they
will enable Raglan to achieve a capital restructuring.
